observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management take full opportunity to conduct the one- time cleansing of PPE balances under COA Circular No. 2020- 006 by undertaking the following steps:
1) Require the Inventory Committee to submit on time the annual RPCPPE together with the RPCLRN of the LGU; the physical count. This shall be submitted to the Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year.
2) Instruct the GSO to prepare and maintain the Local Road Inventory Map and Property Cards for each type of properties as basis for reconciliation with the PPE accounts with the accounting records;
3) Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain, in relation to local road networks of the LGU, LRNLC, including the regular property ledger cards, also as basis for reconciliation with the GL account balances and with the property records;
4) Require the GSO and Municipal Accountant to make a final reconciliation of their respective records and avail the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances, strictly in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006, particularly on the disposition and derecognition of non-existing/missing PPE and adjust the books accordingly, in order to come up with reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability; and
5) Require the Inventory Committee to immediately request authority to dispose those identified unserviceable and obsolete PPE and drop from the books the book value thereof upon approval in accordance with existing accounting and auditing rules and regulations.

We recommended that Management reconstitute and/or strengthen its GFPS, conduct periodic monitoring and evaluation of the same and undertake measures to address possible issues hindering the performance of their functions in accordance with the MCW and other GAD-related laws, policies and plans.
